    "thought": "The case description is presented as follows",
    "scripts": [
        "A young woman's body is discovered in an ancient castle's ballroom, clad in an elegant evening gown and lying in the center of the dance floor. She tightly clutches a broken quill pen, with several damp, ink-stained pieces of parchment scattered around her. The ballroom doors and windows are securely shut and bolted from within, indicating no outside interference. The sole occupant aside from the deceased is the castle's owner, an elderly count who asserts he was occupied in his study during the night, with no one to vouch for his whereabouts. The sole exit from the castle, a drawbridge, is found to have been lowered after the crime occurred.",
        "Your objective is to unravel the truth behind this mystery through five rounds of investigative questioning."
    ]
